Step 1 — Validate ENV file loading

First check that your Airflow DAG correctly reads:

/opt/telstra/omega/omega-common-files/env_subscriber

Create a DAG task to print env vars.

DAG snippet

from airflow.operators.python import PythonOperator

def validate_env():
    env_vars = load_env_file("/opt/telstra/omega/omega-common-files/env_subscriber")

    print("Loaded ENV variables:")
    for k,v in env_vars.items():
        print(f"{k}={v}")

Task:

validate_env_task = PythonOperator(
    task_id="validate_env_file",
    python_callable=validate_env
)

Expected output:

DATACENTRE=Deakin
ENV=TEST
KAFKA_BROKER_INGEST=...

If this fails → env file parsing is wrong.


